---
description: Prefer arrow functions over function declarations
globs: ["*.js", "*.ts", "*.jsx", "*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer arrow functions over traditional function declarations
- Use `const functionName = () => {}` instead of `function functionName() {}`
- Exception: Class methods should remain as methods
- Benefits: Lexical `this` binding, more concise, consistent with modern JS/TS style
